"If you can read it, you can also write it down again. That’s the basic copying mechanism, and that’s how computers work: computers are just basic copying machines. So digital scarcity is an oxymoron; it was never possible before Bitcoin."⁣
⁣
Gigi Der takes us through what is so special about Bitcoin and how it embodies the idea of digital scarcity.⁣
⁣
Learn more about it via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/13/2021 (S4: E39).

"Whether or not your wife does the dishes when she’s supposed to once really doesn’t destabilize you that much, because not much else depends on it. If she did it 10 times, or something like that, then you might start to question her commitment to your agreements. Then you might question her honesty, and then you might question your relationship. You can go down a rabbit hole pretty quickly."⁣
⁣
From my appearance on the "The Tim Ferris Show" - @TimFerriss⁣
⁣
Watch more on YouTube.

node.title: The Psychological Impact of Betrayed Values

"The opportunity cost is infinite to anywhere you place your limited resources. So the journey, or the evolution of money, of finding a money, has been to try to find something that mimics our limitations, that mimics the sacrifices we make when we bestow value on something."⁣
⁣
Another clip from my latest podcast (S4: E40) where we discuss and explore Bitcoin, crypto, and what it means for society with John Vallis, Gigi Der, Robert Breedlove, and Richard James.⁣
⁣
Watch more via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/13/2021.

node.title: Money Is A Measure of Sacrifice

⁣
My guests are John Vallis, Gigi Der, Robert Breedlove, and Richard James.⁣
⁣
Watch this podcast (S4: E40) on YouTube via the link in my bio.⁣
⁣
Recorded 05/13/2021.

⁣

⁣
From my appearance on the "The Tim Ferris Show" - @TimFerriss⁣
⁣
Watch more on YouTube.

@Yeonmi_Park shared her experience escaping North Korea on my podcast (S4: E26). It's available on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, and YouTube.⁣
⁣
Recorded 04/14/2021.

⁣

⁣
Skavlan Show - October 2018.
